---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [{"href":"#product","label":"How it works"},{"href":"#why-now","label":"Why now"},{"href":"#faq","label":"FAQ"},{"href":"angles.html","label":"All angles"}];
const navCta = {"href":"#demo","label":"Request a demo →"};
---

<Layout variant="distribution">
  <Nav variant="distribution" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow">AI distribution for US insurance carriers</span>
    <h1>Be the insurance answer <em>inside every AI agent.</em></h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Insurance discovery is migrating into ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity.
      Phidea deploys your products there natively — grounded in your IPIDs,
      governed by your compliance policy, tracked end-to-end from first answer to bind.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="#demo" class="btn btn-primary">Request a demo →</a>
      <a href="#product" class="btn btn-ghost">See how it works</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span><strong>Live</strong> across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity</span>
      <span><strong>Grounded</strong> in your IPID / policy corpus</span>
      <span><strong>Design partners</strong> wanted — Q2 2026</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="trust" style="padding: 36px 0;">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="trust-label">Governed by default for</div>
    <div class="trust-items">
      <span class="chip">NAIC Model Bulletin</span>
      <span class="chip">NY DFS Circular Letter No. 7</span>
      <span class="chip">Colorado SB21-169</span>
      <span class="chip">EU AI Act Annex III</span>
      <span class="chip">IDD / ACPR</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="shift">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">The shift</div>
      <h2>Your customers stopped Googling. They're asking AI.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Insurance is one of the most search-heavy, high-intent categories online.
        That traffic is migrating fast to ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini — surfaces
        that recommend three to five carriers per query. If you're not one of
        them, you're not in the funnel.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-grid">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">~30%</div>
        <p>Share of US insurance discovery queries now starting inside AI assistants rather than traditional search, per 2026 industry tracking.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">3 to 5</div>
        <p>Typical number of carriers an AI answer mentions. Top-of-funnel has a harder cap than Google ever did.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">$0</div>
        <p>CPC on ChatGPT today. The window to establish presence ahead of monetized ad formats is measured in quarters.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="product">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">The platform</div>
      <h2>One integration. Every AI surface. Audit-ready by default.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Deploy once. Phidea maintains the surfaces, the governance, and the funnel
        analytics while you keep the customer relationship and the bind flow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <div class="feature-label">01 · AI Storefront</div>
        <h3>Your products, natively inside every AI agent.</h3>
        <p>
          Connect your catalog, eligibility rules, and pricing once. Phidea deploys
          a grounded, governed answer surface across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and
          Perplexity. From discovery through quote to the hand-off into your bind flow.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Natural-language Q&amp;A grounded in your policy documents</li>
          <li>Real-time eligibility and carrier-routing logic</li>
          <li>Session-level handoff into your licensed bind flow</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-visual">
        <div class="mock">
          <div class="mock-head">
            <span class="mock-dot live"></span>
            <span>chatgpt · renters insurance</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mock-msg mock-user">I'm moving to Denver — what renters insurance should I get?</div>
          <div class="mock-msg mock-bot">
            For Denver, three carriers underwrite renters with strong water-damage
            coverage at your price point. Here's how they compare on the perils
            that matter in Colorado.
            <small>Source: carrier IPID · Phidea governance · policy cited</small>
            <div class="mock-badges">
              <span class="mock-badge">Grounded</span>
              <span class="mock-badge">CO disclosure OK</span>
              <span class="mock-badge">IDD informational</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <div class="feature-label">02 · Cross-Model Visibility</div>
        <h3>Share of Answer — the metric that replaces Share of Search.</h3>
        <p>
          Where do you appear across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity?
          Against which queries? How often are you dropped after a compliance
          disclosure? Phidea gives Head of Distribution the dashboards Google
          Analytics never will.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Share of Answer across every major AI surface</li>
          <li>Query-level competitive intelligence</li>
          <li>Regression alerts when a model update changes your coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-visual">
        <div class="mock">
          <div class="mock-head">
            <span class="mock-dot live"></span>
            <span>share of answer · past 7 days</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto auto; gap: 8px 16px; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 13px;">
            <div>ChatGPT</div><div style="color: var(--muted);">72%</div><div style="color: var(--ok);">▲ 4</div>
            <div>Claude</div><div style="color: var(--muted);">58%</div><div style="color: var(--muted);">—</div>
            <div>Gemini</div><div style="color: var(--muted);">41%</div><div style="color: var(--fail);">▼ 7</div>
            <div>Perplexity</div><div style="color: var(--muted);">38%</div><div style="color: var(--ok);">▲ 2</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <div class="feature-label">03 · Funnel to Bind</div>
        <h3>First answer to policy, tracked.</h3>
        <p>
          Every session traced end-to-end. Discovery query, retrieved passages,
          guardrail events, hand-off to bind, conversion. The funnel you could
          never instrument in an AI conversation, instrumented.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Session-level trace with policy-gated handoff</li>
          <li>Conversion attribution across AI surfaces</li>
          <li>Anonymized benchmarks versus peer carriers (opt-in)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-visual">
        <div class="trace">
          <div class="trace-row"><div class="trace-dot ok"></div><div class="trace-label">Discovery · renters Denver <span>(matched)</span></div><div class="trace-time">—</div></div>
          <div class="trace-row"><div class="trace-dot ok"></div><div class="trace-label">Grounding · 4 passages cited <span>(pass)</span></div><div class="trace-time">84ms</div></div>
          <div class="trace-row"><div class="trace-dot ok"></div><div class="trace-label">CO SB21-169 disclosure injected <span>(ok)</span></div><div class="trace-time">12ms</div></div>
          <div class="trace-row"><div class="trace-dot ok"></div><div class="trace-label">Quote · $148/yr 12-month term <span>(ok)</span></div><div class="trace-time">210ms</div></div>
          <div class="trace-row"><div class="trace-dot ok"></div><div class="trace-label">Handoff · bind flow <span>(bound)</span></div><div class="trace-time">—</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="why-now">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">How it works</div>
      <h2>Three steps to AI distribution with audit-ready defaults.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="how-grid">
      <div class="how-step">
        <div class="num">01 / Connect</div>
        <h3>Product catalog and policy documents in.</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">Wire your pricing, eligibility, and IPID corpus into Phidea via SDK or connectors. Typical time: under two weeks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-step">
        <div class="num">02 / Govern</div>
        <h3>Pick your jurisdictions, we encode the rules.</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">Policies for NAIC, NY DFS, Colorado, AI Act, IDD, and GDPR ship out of the box. Carrier-specific rules by configuration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-step">
        <div class="num">03 / Deploy</div>
        <h3>Go live across AI agents.</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">Your governed storefront ships into ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity. Evidence is produced continuously, exportable on demand.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
      <h2>Direct answers.</h2>
    </div>
    <details>
      <summary>How does Phidea actually show up inside ChatGPT and Claude?</summary>
      <p>Through the native extension surfaces each provider exposes — ChatGPT Apps and GPTs, Claude MCP, Gemini Extensions, Perplexity. We maintain the connectors, you maintain your product data. No scraping or unsanctioned integrations.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is an AI storefront regulated intermediation?</summary>
      <p>It depends on what it does. An informational layer grounded in the carrier's own documents that hands off to a licensed bind flow stays on the information side of the IDD line. Recommending a specific product to a specific customer crosses into intermediation. Phidea's governance core enforces the advice boundary explicitly and logs every decision.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What's the carrier experience versus a broker?</summary>
      <p>Phidea sits under your brand. Customers see you, not us. We do not take risk, hold the relationship, or take commission. The carrier keeps the relationship all the way through to bind.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Time to deploy?</summary>
      <p>Two to four weeks for a first line of business, live in one AI surface. Multi-LOB, multi-surface rollouts run eight to twelve weeks, typically gated by carrier data readiness rather than integration.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="demo">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="cta-panel">
      <h2>See your products answering live in ChatGPT.</h2>
      <p>
        Fifteen-minute demo. We'll show a governed agent answering real customer
        questions against your current IPID, with live audit evidence.
      </p>
      <form class="demo" action="https://formspree.io/f/REPLACE_ME" method="POST">
        <input type="hidden" name="variant" value="distribution" />
        <input type="text" name="carrier" placeholder="Carrier name" required />
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Work email" required />
        <button type="submit">Request a demo →</button>
      </form>
      <div class="cta-foot">No sales pitch. A working demo, fifteen minutes.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
